A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Institutions of Higher Education – Instructor Training – Accommodations for
3 Students With Disabilities
4 FOR the purpose of requiring certain institutions of higher education to provide instructors
5 with certain training on institutional obligations toward students with disabilities
6 under certain federal laws; requiring the Maryland Higher Education Commission
7 to develop a certain model training program; and generally relating to instructor
8 training on accommodations for students with disabilities and institutions of higher
9 education.
10 BY adding to
11 Article – Education
12 Section 11–409
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Education
18 11–409.
19 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “INSTRUCTOR” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL EMPLOYED BY
20 OR UNDER CONTRACT WITH AN INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION:
21 (1) AS A TENURED OR NONTENURED PROFESSOR, AN INSTRUCTOR,
22 OR A TEACHING ASSISTANT; OR
