2 HOUSE BILL 912
1 (2) TO PROVIDE DIRECT INSTRUCTION TO STUDENTS.
2 (B) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO AN INSTITUTION OF HIGHER
3 EDUCATION THAT HAS AN EXISTING TRAINING ON THE LEGAL OBLIGATIONS OF THE
4 INSTITUTION TOWARD STUDENTS WITH DISABILITIES UNDER THE FEDERAL
5 AMERICANS WITH DISABILITIES ACT AND SECTION 504 OF THE REHABILITATION
6 ACT THAT MEETS THE STANDARDS REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS
7 SECTION.
8 (C) (1) BEGINNING IN THE 2026–2027 ACADEMIC YEAR, EACH
9 INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION SHALL PROVIDE TO INSTRUCTORS OF THE
10 INSTITUTION TRAINING ON THE LEGAL OBLIGATIONS OF THE INSTITUTION TOWARD
11 STUDENTS WITH DISABILITIES UNDER THE FEDERAL AMERICANS WITH
12 DISABILITIES ACT AND SECTION 504 OF THE REHABILITATION ACT, INCLUDING
13 INFORMATION ON ACADEMIC ACCOMMODATIONS AND ADJUSTMENTS FOR
14 QUALIFIED STUDENTS.
15 (2) THE TRAINING REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
16 SUBSECTION SHALL BE:
17 (I) PROVIDED TO INSTRUCTORS BY THE INSTITUTION OF
18 HIGHER EDUCATION IN PERSON OR VIRTUALLY; AND
19 (II) PROVIDED TO AND COMPLETED BY:
20 1. A NEW INSTRUCTOR BEFORE THE INSTRUCTOR
21 BEGINS TEACHING STUDENTS; AND
22 2. A CURRENTLY EMPLOYED INSTRUCTOR ON OR
23 BEFORE OCTOBER 1, 2026.
24 (D) THE COMMISSION SHALL DEVELOP A MODEL TRAINING PROGRAM FOR
25 THE INFORMATION REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION THAT MAY
26 BE USED BY INSTITUTIONS OF HIGHER EDUCATION THROUGHOUT THE STATE.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
28 1, 2025.

